    <center><h2 style="color:white;">About Turn the Tide</h2></center>
    <p class="about-text">Turn the Tide was developed as a senior project by Team A-F14 for the School of Computing
    at the University of Utah.  With special thanks to Kerry Kelly, a research associate at the Institute of Secure
    & Clean Energy at the U of U, and her insight and expertise about Utah's air quality, we decided to create an 
    application that would provide a step towards solving a real-life problem.  As residents of the Wasatch Front, each member of the team
    is familiar with the inversions that descend upon the valleys during the winter.  This provided us with a common 
    goal of clearing our air; one where we hope that by accomplishing, we can breathe the air a little easier.</p>
